---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Visions on the Path">
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>About Visions on the Path</h1>
            <p>Our intention is simplicity: remove what's not needed, support what is, and invite quiet transformation through the practice of Kriya Yoga.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-grid">
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
            <p>We believe in direct experience over dogma, practice over theory, and inner silence over outer noise.
            Kriya Yoga is a practical science for the modern seeker.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">Rooted in tradition, relevant today</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>What is Kriya Yoga?</h2>
            <p>An ancient meditation technique focused on breath, energy, and awareness.
            It systematically calms the mind and awakens deeper states of consciousness.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">Suitable for all backgrounds</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
            <p>Anyone seeking clarity, peace, and spiritual growth. No prior experience needed—just openness,
            consistency, and a willingness to observe yourself honestly.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">Beginners welcome</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>The Approach</h2>
            <p>Clean design. Clear instruction. No clutter. We focus on what matters: your practice,
            your breath, and your gradual unfolding into stillness.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">Minimalist and accessible</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="featured">
        <div class="featured-content">
            <h2>Our Lineage</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                    Visions on the Path honors the Kriya Yoga lineage passed down through Mahavatar Babaji,
                    Lahiri Mahasaya, Sri Yukteswar, and Paramahansa Yogananda. We draw from this profound
                    tradition while presenting the teachings in a clear, contemporary format suitable for
                    modern practitioners navigating busy lives.
                </p>
                <p class="card-meta" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    Based in practice, informed by lineage, designed for you.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
